<TITLE> ECB team due in Dhaka for security checks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 22 (bdnews24.com)  A two-member delegation from the England Cricket Board arrived in Dhaka on Wednesday to assess security and facilities ahead of the England U-19 and national team tour of Bangladesh. England U-19 will visit Bangladesh from October-November to play their Bangladesh counterparts, while the senior team will arrive in February next year to play two Tests and three one-day internationals against Bangladesh. The delegation consisting of ECB cricket operations director John Donald Carr and security consultant Reginal Clyde Dickason is scheduled to visit Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium and Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan on Wednesday, said BCB media manager Rabeed Imam. They will visit Narayanganj Fatullah Stadium on Thursday before going on to Chittagong on Friday to inspect Chittagong Divisional Stadium. The delegation will also meet BCB and government officials during the three-day visit before departing Saturday. bdn
